                        <p id="ans1" class="interview_ans mb-0"><i
                              class="fa fa-arrow-right text-primary me-2"></i>Database management systems were developed to handle the following difficulties of typical File-processing systems supported by conventional operating systems. 
                              <br>1. Data redundancy and inconsistency 
                              <br>2. Difficulty in accessing data 
                              <br>3. Data isolation – multiple files and formats 
                              <br>4. Integrity problems 
                              <br>5. Atomicity of updates 
                              <br>6. Concurrent access by multiple users 
                              <br>7. Security problems </p>
